NetworkChuck 24 Websites Contest Terms and Conditions
NO PURCHASE NECESSARY TO ENTER OR WIN. A PURCHASE DOES NOT INCREASE YOUR CHANCES OF WINNING.

By participating in the contest, you agree to these official rules.

1. Eligibility
The contest is open to legal residents worldwide who are 18 years or older. Employees of NetworkChuck, its affiliates, subsidiaries, advertising and promotion agencies, and suppliers, (collectively the “Employees”), and immediate family members and/or those living in the same household as Employees are not eligible to participate. Void where prohibited.

2. Contest Period
The contest begins on the release date of the NetworkChuck video titled “I Created 24 Websites...” and ends when the prizes are claimed. NetworkChuck reserves the right to end the contest earlier or extend it as necessary.

3. How to Enter
Entry details are provided in the corresponding NetworkChuck YouTube video. No purchase is necessary to enter or win. To participate, follow the instructions within the video, which include finding secret phrases on websites and submitting your email through a designated Google Form or being the first to submit your email when a timer expires.

4. Prizes
A total of four (4) $500 Amazon gift cards will be awarded. One (1) $500 Amazon gift card will be awarded to the first individual to submit their email once the timer expires on the designated website. Three (3) $500 Amazon gift cards will be awarded to the first three individuals to submit their email and name after solving the secret phrase puzzle across 23 websites.

Prizes will be delivered via email within 30 days of the contest's conclusion. NetworkChuck reserves the right to substitute a prize of equal or greater value if necessary.

5. Winner Selection and Notification
The winners will be the first participants to correctly complete the tasks outlined in the video, either by submitting their email when the timer expires or by correctly solving the secret phrase challenge. Winners will be notified via email using the email address provided. If a winner does not respond within 48 hours of the notification, an alternate winner may be selected.

6. Disqualification
NetworkChuck reserves the right to disqualify any participant found to be tampering with the contest entry process or websites, including the use of bots, automated systems, or hacking techniques. Any attempt to deliberately damage or undermine the legitimate operation of the contest may be a violation of criminal and civil laws. NetworkChuck reserves the right to seek damages to the fullest extent permitted by law.

7. Privacy
By participating in the contest, you agree that your email and personal information will only be used for the purposes of administering this contest and notifying winners. NetworkChuck will not share or sell your information to third parties.

8. Limitation of Liability
NetworkChuck is not responsible for lost, late, misdirected, or undeliverable entries, or for any technical issues that may prevent an entry from being submitted or received. By entering, participants agree to release and hold harmless NetworkChuck from any and all liability, injury, loss, or damage of any kind resulting from participation in this contest or from the acceptance, possession, or use of any prize awarded.

9. Sponsor Information
This contest is sponsored solely by NetworkChuck. Amazon is not a sponsor, nor is it affiliated with this contest in any way.

10. Governing Law
This contest is governed by the laws of the state of Texas, USA. Any disputes arising from this contest shall be adjudicated in the courts of Texas.

Agreement to Rules
By participating, you agree to be fully and unconditionally bound by these rules, and you represent and warrant that you meet the eligibility requirements.
